Deep Footprint in High-Growth Markets
Our high-quality portfolio of over 30,000 single-family rental homes is concentrated in a limited number of targeted U.S. markets characterized by favorable long-term demand/supply fundamentals. With an average of over 2,800 homes in each of our top ten markets, our strategy of building market density drives operational efficiencies.
Our advantages of cost of capital, operating scale, management expertise and technology platforms allow us to operate at higher margins while producing superior returns on equity over a large portfolio.



Click on a state to view more.


																	
								CLICK HERE TO VIEW RENTAL HOMES CURRENTLY AVAILABLE										
																	







LOS ANGELES, CALIFORNIA




										Our History									

Our History
We recognized the unique opportunity created by the housing crisis and acted upon it in a bold way. Our disciplined market and asset selection strategies created a concentrated portfolio of valuable assets with strong future growth prospects. We then renovated, leased and stabilized over 30,000 homes across our targeted market footprint, improving homes, neighborhoods and providing families with high quality housing options along the way.  We attracted some of the best talent in the real estate arena and developed unique and highly scalable leading-edge technologies that embrace our customers, enable our employees and help us produce steadily improving and predictable results. The January, 2016 merger of our two predecessor companies, Colony American Homes and Starwood Waypoint Residential Trust, demonstrated the effectiveness and scalability of our combined platform.




CHARLOTTE, NORTH CAROLINA





										Technology									

Technology – 
Atlas, our proprietary technology platform, is a web-based, mobile-friendly and highly scalable software system with functionality across multiple departments, including Acquisitions/Dispositions, Leasing, Construction & Maintenance and Asset Management. Atlas enables our associates to be more efficient by being fully integrated with the technology systems of over 40 of our outside vendors. It also engages our residents by providing a mobile-enabled lease application and completion process, a seamless online rent payment capability, and a service portal with detailed self-help videos. Atlas is revolutionizing the single-family rental industry.




ATLANTA, GEORGIA




										Asset Management									

Asset Management
Our asset management and investment teams are armed with experience and technologies that continue to find attractive yielding investments across multiple channels. Unique to our industry, we have a dedicated revenue management team which focuses on optimizing revenue by evaluating market conditions, competitive sets and submarket-specific portfolio performance. This enables us to effectively manage lease expiration schedules by individual market according to seasonally adjusted pricing and consumer demand.





TAMPA, FLORIDA




										Positioned for Growth									

Positioned for Growth
A tremendous frontier lies ahead – the consolidation of the highly fragmented single family rental industry. The addressable market is in excess of 16 million rental homes, of which institutional owners like Colony Starwood Homes currently control a very small fraction. Going forward, we plan to engage in a meaningful but disciplined growth strategy that will continue to strengthen our balance sheet and reward our shareholders well into the future.




HOUSTON, TEXAS























